		<div class="comment-content" itemprop="commentText">
			
			<p>Thanks, David. If BTC (or something like BTC) becomes widely used and replaces fiat money then it could be complementary to gold for some time but not forever. &#8216;Complementary&#8217; monies or competing monies are suboptimal arrangements. Ultimately, one form of money wins, and that could indeed be BTC, or inelastic, unmanipulated digital money. Conceptually and in the long run, gold faces its first true challenger in a few thousand years.</p>
		</div>

